	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			This spell is the first upgrade to the 'projectile' spells for wizards.  Its very long ranged, and very powerful, although not as mana efficient as later bolts.  It starts at 45 damage, and gains one per level until it maxes at 51.<BR>
<BR>
Its range allows the caster to often fire as many as three of them before even entering hand-to-hand combat.  In some cases, the range is far enough that the enemy creature cannot figure out which way to move and chase you, therefore allowing you to strike with impunity.  The best example of such a situation, that I've run across, is at the top of the chasm in Blackburrow -- you can fire bolts from one side to the other, and the targetted gnoll will often just... sit there. =)<BR>
<BR>
As a side note, the firey bolt will appear to travel across the entire zone on many occasions, but will only deal damage to its range limit.
			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
