	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Firebolt is a must have for all wizards. This spell is very &quot;guided&quot;, if u are facing the completely opposite way of your target and cast this spell, you will see the firebolt make a complete circle around you and hit the target head on. If this spell is casted at a rather close range to your target you will see the target combust (shock of fire effect) and it will be hit for 45 dmg. before the bolt even touches the target. If you are at a rather far range from the target, the target will not combust but will be hit for 45dmg. when hit by the firebolt. I suggest that you use firebolt to lure the target and then cast &quot;shock of ice&quot; before it gets to you. I recommend not to root a target if you are planning on using firebolt because it will most likely knock the target loose. 
			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
